<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<ecoSpold xmlns="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02 ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02.xsd http://www.EcoInvent.org/UsedUserMasterData ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02UserMasterData.xsd">
  <childActivityDataset>
    <activityDescription>
      <activity specialActivityType="0" id="7a4c899b-ceb4-5d46-aa0b-b45a342f536f" activityNameId="f134f119-59c4-43cf-a777-05cad7011899" parentActivityId="cda2a9a4-050c-4d15-9764-82af9d68e525" inheritanceDepth="-1" type="1">
        <activityName xml:lang="en">plasticiser production, for concrete, based on sulfonated melamine formaldehyde</activityName>
        <includedActivitiesStart xml:lang="en">The activity starts with the ingredients for the plasticiser at the factory gate. The values on energy consumption are generic data (see respective comments fields".</includedActivitiesStart>
        <includedActivitiesEnd xml:lang="en">The dataset contains a rough bill of materials for the production of the plasticiser.</includedActivitiesEnd>
        <generalComment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">Plasticisers or water reducers, and superplasticiser or high range water reducers, are chemical admixtures that can be added to concrete mixtures to improve workability. Unless the mix is "starved" of water, the strength of concrete is inversely proportional to the amount of water added or water-cement (w/c) ratio. In order to produce stronger concrete, less water is added (without "starving" the mix), which makes the concrete mixture less workable and difficult to mix, necessitating the use of plasticisers, water reducers, superplasticisers or dispersants.</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="1">Plasticisers are commonly manufactured from lignosulfonates, a by-product from the paper industry. Superplasticisers have generally been manufactured from sulfonated naphthalene condensate or sulfonated melamine formaldehyde, although newer products based on polycarboxylic ethers are now available. </text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="2"></text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="3">This dataset contains the production of a plasticiser for concrete based on sulfonated melamine formaldehyde.</text>
        </generalComment>
      </activity>
      <classification classificationId="28f738cc-bb73-48f8-b633-f83fb9bc5ddc">
        <classificationSystem xml:lang="en">ISIC rev.4 ecoinvent</classificationSystem>
        <classificationValue xml:lang="en">2011:Manufacture of basic chemicals</classificationValue>
      </classification>
      <geography geographyId="34dbbff8-88ce-11de-ad60-0019e336be3a">
        <shortname xml:lang="en">GLO</shortname>
      </geography>
      <technology technologyLevel="3"/>
      <timePeriod startDate="2014-01-01" endDate="2023-12-31" isDataValidForEntirePeriod="true"/>
      <macroEconomicScenario macroEconomicScenarioId="d9f57f0a-a01f-42eb-a57b-8f18d6635801">
        <name xml:lang="en">Business-as-Usual</name>
      </macroEconomicScenario>
    </activityDescription>
